They took care of us very well and also made us Vegan Malasadas. The chef has amazing culinary skills and their menu has variety of options. Loved the food so much and their service is amazing. I went to eat there for the first time and can’t recommend it less. First of all I asked if they had wraps and the lady told me that she could do any sandwich as a wrap. So I told her I wanted half of a wrap (as you can buy half of a sandwich) but she said that wraps can only be sold as an entire one. I ordered an entire wrap and added tempeh for $1 more . It arrived as a sandwich and I asked them to please change it because it wasn’t what I had ordered and they made me pay  $1.5 to change it for a wrap (and I did even though I wasn’t told before). It arrived again, this time as a wrap but without tofu. When I asked for the tofu she told me they changed the tofu for the tempeh. It was SO SALTY that I couldn’t  finish it, They gave me a cake because of all the problems, and I’ve never tried something worse. While trying the cake I started feeling so bad of my stomach and had to go straight home. I’m now in bed after vomiting. WORST EXPERIENCE EVER. I would’ve given 0 stars if I could.

Exceedingly friendly and most of the food was great (the carrot side was not entirely to my taste). But I've got to say, when they're imitating American meat standards (I ordered their holiday special, which seemed to be aiming for turkey with sides), the results are like they've had the food described to them in not-quite-great-enough-depth detail and done their best to make and, and make it tasty. This place has a ton of potential, and I am very sad that I will probably not be coming here again.  The food here is great.   My favorite dish is the BBQ Tempeh Sandwich.   However, our order was messed up so many times that even the greatest food is not worth the frustration.  One time I got a tempeh dish instead of my delicious tempeh sandwich.   Not a big deal, I can live with that, the dish was still pretty good.   Another time we we were hoping for a quick lunch during work break.   The quick lunch turned into a half an hour wait for food.   When I finally inquired about the delay, they realized they forgot our order and gave us our food to go.   While in the car we found out that the order was messed up.   Also, their to go dishes seem to be smaller than the dishes served in the restaurant.  Another time we pre-ordered our food to avoid the wait.   We intended to eat in the restaurant, but we were given food packed to go, which completely ruined our dining experience.   Oh, did I mentioned that the to go portions were smaller than the normal dishes?  Our last visit was worst of them all.  We came to the restaurant with three hungry kids.  We were starving after a long hike.   Can you imagine waiting for food with hungry kids?   Let me tell, it wasn't pleasant.   The restaurant was not too busy, and our family of five took up the entire table right in the front of the cash register girl who took our order.   Not even once during our 45 min wait for our  food did she wonder what were we doing there.   I guess it is normal for a family of five to just sit in Peace Cafe taking up the entire huge table with just water on the front of them.  During the 45 min that we were waiting for our food, at least three Bite Squad delivery drivers came to pick up their food orders.   I realized that if we ordered our food through Bite Squad we would have gotten it.   So sad.  Two stars because the food normally is great.  This time we didn't get to eat at all.  We will not be risking coming back here again.

Awesome vegan selection with a great staff. Solid price point and the portion are actually large enough to make you full. I typically get something to eat there and take something home. Delicious 100% vegan entrees and drinks! It was the perfect breakfast on our vacation! The place has quality food and personality. It felt like home but better because of the amazing food. We had the Italian sandwich and the Tofu scramble plate which came with salad, soup, and yummy bread. The tofu scramble was uniquely creamy and rich. We also loved the black sesame latte and sundae with one scoop each of matcha and chocolate, berry sauce, and granola. Definitely want to go back!
Great food, decent prices (not too expensive). All vegan and the atmosphere was great. I loved their japanese mochi brownies especially!
Fantastic healthy vegan food. The lemonade was goood.
Amazing vegan food! Kind service. Truely enjoied finding this resturant.
Awesome discovery! Lots of healyhy and vegan options.
Great, small and sympathetic restaurant with tasteful dishes. We came here everyday during our holidays and enjoyed every meal.
Super friendly, great food

Delicious vegan dishes. Had the Katsu plate- $13.00. Came with several slices of tempeh (you can choose between tempeh and tofu) Katsu, sprout/mixed greens salad, tomato, cucumber and a heap of brown/black rice medley. Very filling. Also ordered the super greens smoothie and it’s very fruity with a nice texture.  If we had more time in town we would definitely come back.
Highly recommended for vegetarian and vegan folks and especially for anyone wanting to explore how delicious plant-based eating can be!
Beautiful food and atmosphere and the people that work there are very kind.

The Yogini bowl/plate is a favorite of mine as well as the varieties of mochi brownies. Wonderful people too and extremely helpful if you're a veg n and new to the island. We picked up the ThanksLiving dinner to share with friends last year and thoroughly enjoyed it.
Very homely. Casual atmosphere. Food is tasty & healthy.
Decent portioned vegan food at ok prices ($20-25 for two entrees / salads / sandwiches). Vegan ice cream was also available in mint chocolate and coconut flavors at $3 a scoop plus toppings.

It’s our new favorite place to eat. Since switching to a veggietarian diet I haven’t found a place to take my wife out that we can really enjoy until now. So delicious and I love trying new things. So glad we found peace cafe

The bread was fresh and so were all the veggies on it.  NOTE:  since everything here is fresh, they run out of some menu items, so if you have your heart set on a particular item, you might want to give them a call before you head over there.

Peace Cafe is an awesome vegan spot. They have great plates and sandwiches. Also, I really appreciate how they try to change out the menu. They also have dessert options. I wish they would update their website to show their daily specials.. parking is in the back or you can street park.
Best vegan food on Oahu.
Delicious vegan food and wonderful options. We love the Popeye sandwich.

The food was amazing. Its a very small hole in the wall off of king street very easy to miss, so make sure you are looking. Once in the place if no one is behind the counter be sure to ring the bell so they know there is someone new. My favorite plate is the poke bowl.  But the peace plate is also very delicious and healthy.  I haven't tried their sandwiches but the people next to me were eating them so that will be a next for me. A place to eat healthy.

Peace Cafe is located between the McCully library and the old stadium park. There is no parking lot so only street parking is available. Try and come a little early or a little late to beat the lunch rush. We arrived around 10:30 a.m. and easily found street parking in front of the restaurant. The pay meters are $0.25 for 20 minutes. At that time, the restaurant was nearly empty. We chose a quiet table in the back close to the restaurants mini Library.  Shortly after sitting down we were greeted by a friendly waitress who brought our menus and explain many things. I told her it was my first is it to her restaurant and only my second visit to a vegan restaurant so I needed some help in choosing things. She recommended the Popeye sandwich and the bibimbap for some variety. We also had their house made lemonade and iced tea and those two drinks were really amazing. You might need a little Agave to sweeten your Ice-T though.  To complete our meal we finished with a matcha Brownie and the hot coffee. The tab was about $35 plus tip. It's very good for the freshness and health that you are choosing. Definitely recommended.
Tasty beautiful food, great atmosphere with friendly happy people.  Definitely a place I want to spend some time.

Not a vegetarian, but Peace Cafe could definitely turn me into one. I LOVE this place!!! Their sandwiches are SO DELICIOUS!!! And my favorite drink is their kinako latte.

Like stepping back into the 90’s? I do. There aren’t many places like Peace Cafe anymore on island or anywhere, sadly. Crunchy vegetarian food, delicious and the servings are generous.  They also have great coconut milk ice cream, smoothies and baked goods.

Food is decent. Got a green onion miso sandwich that was on special. Pretty tasty even to my omnivore family. Had a peanut type sauce taste to it. Restaurant had run out of Tempeh at the time otherwise I would have gotten something else. This sandwich had tofu. Got cornbread also which was ok, had a strong flavor which I can't place. Affogato was also good. Food came out pretty quick. Place wasnt too busy. Just two other customers. Cute little restaurant. I'd go again to try something else and hopefully they would have what I want when I go.
Friendly service in sweet homey cafe setting. A variety of yummy vegan eats and great options for Celiacs. Yay!  Can't wait to return!

I loved the homemade atmosphere of this place. Super cute and comfortable. I was greeted right away by a girl at the counter and she was patient and helpful as I looked through the menu, which has so many options. I couldn't decide as I wanted to try everything. I was so happy to find an all vegan restaurant in Oahu. I ended up getting the poke bowl, which was made with tofu. OMG it was delicious! So much flavor! My daughter got the tofu terriyaki sandwich, which can also be made with tempeh. It was flavorful and my 6-year-old loved it! After we were stuffed from eating we still decided to order the homemade vanilla and chocolate ice cream. It was quite expensive for such a tiny scoop. Don't expect giant ice cream scoops. It was good but for the price but I probably wouldn't get it again. Overall, I can't wait to go back to this place and try other items in their menu.

Yummy food, very fresh, reasonable wait time for meal, lots of creative food options, friendly staff. Mouth still waters thinking about The Hanoi (one of the sandwiches). Also, they provide awesome condiments.

I'm not on this side of town very often so I've only been here once. I ordered a green smoothie. It was nice and thick and cold, the way I like it. The staff is friendly and from what I saw on other customers' plates looked fresh and plated well.
Amazing food but tough to find a seat if it's busy.

Peace Cafe is a great vegan restaurant with wonderful food, a friendly staff, and a cute vibe. Even my friends who are not vegetarians like myself greatly enjoy the food and the atmosphere! In my opinion, what makes this restaurant special are its sauces--all of which are made fresh at the restaurant with their unique own recipes--and the fresh, high quality ingredients that they use. I highly recommend this restaurant!
Delicious tempeh and nice potions
The food was diverse, and had a lot of tempeh and quinoa ingredients. Their ice cream was amazing! I love the candied nuts in the sundae.

Hands down my favorite vegan restaurant in Oahu! I love how creative and healthy the menu is. The staff is lovely, and the food is consistently delicious! I love the ocean bowl with fresh seaweed, veggies, tofu, rice and yummy sauce also the yogini is one of my favs! I've tried almost every item on the menu and wasn't disappointed! Love peace cafe! Try their ice cream  with espresso Thanks Peace cafe!
Amazing food. Ate here twice in two days. Staff was great!

Not many options for vegan dining in Waikiki, but if you travel a short distance away from the bustle of the beach to S King St, there are a few to choose from. We opted for Peace Cafe and weren't disappointed. It's a pretty casual dining experience,  but the staff were really friendly and the food was excellent (the Moroccan stew was outstanding).  Highly recommended for vegans/vegetarians or anyone looking for something less touristy than the rest of Waikiki has to offer.

Big portions, but somewhat bland. The same slightly-sweet bread was used for the Honoi sandwich and the Ceasar salad.

Wonderful!!!  On a recent trip to Honolulu, we passed a little sign that read "Peace Cafe vegan home Cooking".  We stopped in. The staff were super nice, and the owner and his wife came out to see if everything was ok!  The menu is great, offering a wide variety. I highly recommend it, and I will go back on my next trip!

I am visiting from New York and this place is my favorite, by far that I have found in Hawaii. Lovely staff and the food was so amazing , way better than most vegan restaurants in Ny . You can taste that the food was lovingly made. I will definately be eating here at least once a day. Plus the prices are so fair. May this place have abundant success!!!

Swung by to grab deserts for my wife. Got some moshi cakes, vegan ice cream, and vegan cheesecake. Very casual place, not forcefully vegan, just a nice clean menu of salads and small plates. Small inside, but enough room for a small group to sit together.
The food was excellent. The Hanoi sandwich was great as well as the Moroccan stew. My wife loved the text mex.
Fantastic and very thoughtful food. Excellent service and welcoming atmosphere.

Lovely place run by peaceful folks. The "Heart and Seoul" was pretty health-foody. The taco rice, while not junk food by any means, was awesome and I expect anyone would enjoy it. Followed that with a sundae of homemade vegan ice cream, sweet but not too sweet, and left feeling happy and, yes, peaceful.

What a great little find. My partner and I had the Moroccan stew for dinner and it hit the spot! So nice to see a really good business-one that is ethical, local and provides delicious, healthy food! Great prices too.

I was very pleased with managements response to honor my gift certificate from previous owner..It has renewed my faith in this establishment to uphold the integrity by honoring it's customers. Any establishment that displays its highest regards toward customers will indeed provide nothing less than the very best.. Love their sandwiches!!  Much Aloha & Peace, David

Amazingly simple cafe, with excellent coffee! The vegan ice cream was amazing, and was not dhort at all on flavour. The decor was perfect for the setting. The price was nice, especially for vegan, and especially for Hawaii. Service was great, I literally have nothing bad to say about the place besides that the AC was broken on a hot day :P
The heart and Seoul was amazing! I loved the casual atmosphere.
